The paper focuses on the use of autonomous robotic vehicles for last-mile delivery systems, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The proposed approach involves utilizing deep learning-based image-to-image translation for planning in unmapped environments, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of exploration-based planning algorithms, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the implementation of the proposed algorithm on a vehicle, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
